# 10) CAMERA GRID SYSTEM

Build around five core cameras.

---

## Camera A — Entry Hero Cam
### Purpose
First impression.

### Position
- front-center
- low angle
- sees entry lane, saucer, throne

### Motion
- slow forward dolly
- subtle lateral drift

### Must Show
- saucer silhouette
- AFL branding
- at least one robot
- enough negative space for UI

---

## Camera B — Main Orbit Cam
### Purpose
Website idle loop hero shot.

### Position
- medium-wide orbit around Z3
- high enough to show left and right flanks
- low enough to preserve scale

### Motion
- slow orbit
- very smooth
- subtle rise/fall optional

### Must Show
- saucer
- throne
- cover fields
- one sponsor pillar

---

## Camera C — Saucer Detail Cam
### Purpose
Showcase hero prop quality.

### Position
- closer lens
- side-front angle
- lower than eye line

### Motion
- short arc or slow push

### Must Show
- hull damage
- weapon mount
- energy glow
- robot scale reference

---

## Camera D — Investor CTA Cam
### Purpose
Supports text overlays and sign-up call to action.

### Position
- stable, balanced frame
- throne and saucer visible
- negative space on one side

### Must Show
- premium environment
- readability for text
- clean composition

---

## Camera E — Robot Showcase Cam
### Purpose
Show off the branded robot skin.

### Position
- medium shot
- use backlight or edge light
- keep environment recognizable but secondary

### Must Show
- robot branding
- enough arena context to stay on-theme

