# 11) HERO SHOT COMPOSITION RULES

Every final camera should follow these principles:

## Rule 1
The saucer is always the anchor unless the shot is specifically about the robot.

## Rule 2
The throne must remain visually important but secondary.

## Rule 3
At least one strong diagonal element should exist in wide shots.

## Rule 4
Do not center everything perfectly. Use controlled asymmetry.

## Rule 5
Leave negative space for UI when the shot is intended for the site.

## Rule 6
Every shot must still read “AFL” without text.

